Requirements:
- Wire CometChat into {kind}: auth-token flow, user login, conversation list, 1:1 send/receive; calls if in scope.
- **BACKEND AUTH — login MUST PROVISION the CometChat user before minting its auth token.** The app's
  `POST /api/auth/login` mints a CometChat auth token for the account. But SEEDED / demo accounts (and any
  pre-existing DB user) exist ONLY in the app DB — never in CometChat — so minting a token for them 404s and
  returns "". An empty token makes `CometChatUIKit.login({{authToken:""}})` fail → the chat page NEVER LOADS
  for any real user (compile + a rigged chat-test pair still pass green — this is a classic false-positive).
  FIX: call an idempotent CometChat `createUser` for the user in the SHARED
  login+signup response path. CAUTION — "already exists" is NOT 409: CometChat's POST /v3/users returns
  **HTTP 400 with error.code `ERR_UID_ALREADY_EXISTS`** for a duplicate uid. Branch on that error CODE
  (accept 200/201, plus 409 OR 400-with-ERR_UID_ALREADY_EXISTS). A 409-only check is NOT idempotent: the
  first login for a uid succeeds and EVERY later login throws, so returning users silently get an empty
  token and their chat dies. Log the response BODY on failure — a bare status cannot distinguish
  already-exists from a credentials/payload error. Do this in the SHARED
  login+signup response path, BEFORE minting the token — not just on signup. So every login self-heals the
  account into CometChat. Verify by asserting a demo login's response has a NON-EMPTY cometchat_auth_token.
- Namespace every UID/GUID with "{slug}-". Map RBAC roles → CometChat tags/groups.
- Minimal, idiomatic diff. No unrelated refactors. NO secrets committed (keys in env only).
